---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Roberto Carli" description="Meet Roberto Carli, CMS-certified sommelier based in Redwood City, CA, specializing in wine education and consulting.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-8">About Roberto</h1>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
      <div class="md:col-span-2 prose prose-stone max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
          I'm Roberto Carli, a CMS-certified sommelier based in Redwood City, California. I've spent the better part of two decades immersed in the world of wine — from the vineyards of Piedmont to the tasting rooms of Napa, from the cellars of Burgundy to the dinner tables of the Bay Area.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">My Journey</h2>
        <p>
          I grew up in a family where wine wasn't a luxury — it was part of the meal. My grandfather kept a modest cantina in northern Italy, and some of my earliest memories involve watching him decant a dusty bottle of Barolo for Sunday lunch. That early imprint never left me.
        </p>
        <p>
          After relocating to the United States, I pursued formal training through the Court of Master Sommeliers (CMS), earning my Certified Sommelier credential. The CMS program is one of the most rigorous in the industry, combining blind tasting proficiency, deep theoretical knowledge, and professional service standards.
        </p>
        <p>
          I've worked the floor at fine-dining restaurants in San Francisco, managed wine programs for boutique hotels, and consulted for tech companies building out their hospitality offerings. Today, I focus entirely on education and private consulting — helping people discover what makes wine endlessly fascinating.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">My Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          Wine culture can feel exclusionary. Arcane terminology, intimidating price points, and a perception that you need decades of experience to "get it" — all of this creates barriers. My mission is to dissolve those barriers.
        </p>
        <p>
          I believe the best wine is the one you enjoy, and the best way to learn is by tasting with intention. Every session I lead — whether it's a relaxed home tasting or a corporate masterclass — is designed to build confidence and deepen appreciation without pretension.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Credentials & Training</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Certified Sommelier</strong> — Court of Master Sommeliers, Americas</li>
          <li><strong>WSET Level 3 Award in Wines</strong> — Wine & Spirit Education Trust</li>
          <li><strong>Italian Wine Scholar</strong> — Wine Scholar Guild</li>
          <li>Member, Guild of Sommeliers Education Foundation</li>
          <li>Regular contributor to Bay Area wine education programs</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Beyond the Glass</h2>
        <p>
          When I'm not tasting or teaching, you'll find me hiking the trails around Redwood City, cooking Italian food for friends, or planning my next trip to a wine region I haven't explored yet. I'm currently obsessed with the volcanic wines of Mount Etna and the emerging natural wine scene in the Jura.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-100 to-stone-200 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center sticky top-24">
          <div class="text-6xl mb-4">🍷</div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">Roberto Carli</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">CMS-Certified Sommelier</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">Redwood City, CA</p>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-left">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 font-bold">✓</span>
              <span class="text-stone-600">Court of Master Sommeliers</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 font-bold">✓</span>
              <span class="text-stone-600">WSET Level 3</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 font-bold">✓</span>
              <span class="text-stone-600">Italian Wine Scholar</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="/contact" class="mt-6 inline-block bg-amber-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-amber-700 transition-colors">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
